             <h1 class=""> Structure</h1>
             <h2>Wrapper</h2>
             <p class="intro">When using a fixed navbar at the top and a fixed footer as in this example all the content of the site should be wrapped in a <strong>wrapper</strong>. This adds a margin top and bottom so that the content doesn't hide behind them. This can be adjusted in the structure.scss file.</p>

             <hr class="dashed-client">
             
             <h2>Grid Structure</h2>
             <p class="intro">The Grid Structure has been amended slightly from the Bootstrap Default. We have adjusted the column-gutters to be <strong>20px</strong> instead of the original 30px.</p>
             <p class="text-danger"><strong>Note:</strong> To revert to the default Bootstrap setting, comment out the section <strong>GRID ADJUSTMENTS</strong> in global/structure.scss
             <br/>You will also need to make adjustments in the megamenu.scss (overrides) to align it with the navbar.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
